				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thefriendlyvandal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2064544); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2064544&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183096" alt="thefriendlyvandal" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2064544)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thefriendlyvandal" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2064544); return false;" >thefriendlyvandal</a></span> <span class="odate time_1486598184 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Feb 2017 23:56</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2743210">
									

<p>The Endosymbiotic theory of evolution in Biology explains why chloroplasts and mitochondria have such similar structures to modern E-coli and bacteria cells. The theory states that somewhere along our evolutionary line, bacteria entered into early cells and found it was more beneficial to mooch off of the cell then kill it. Overtime they developed a mutually beneficial relationship, and then fused to become one creature (the mitochondria provides energy to the cell, and the cell provides everything else to the mitochondria). Neither can live on their own as they once were.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Spoiler</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;Spoiler</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>173 came into existence around a child, who was originally modified accordingly by an unknown party to live in it. As the child grew inside the cement, his body became contorted to fit; he knows nothing but this existence. Waste flows out through a tube, and he eats the food that 173 provides for him in exchange for&#8230;</p>
<p>&#8230;:)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A lot of the story isn't told. Maybe it's been lost to time. Maybe not. Maybe it was just a parent looking for the safest way of life for their child.</p>

							</div>

								
