														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2743231">
									

<p>This isn't a story, really. It's more an excuse to make someone imagine how unpleasant it would be to be stuck in a concrete lump and force-fed raw meat, which puts this into kind of the same territory as a torture porn genre movie. And in that function, I don't find myself moved a whole lot, since as a reader I'm just sort of dropped into this scene without context and for no apparent narrative purpose.</p>
<p>I'm also generally uninterested when people use articles as a vehicle to dump their personal interpretations of what things are, without any real structure around it beyond &quot;hey, here's what I think this is.&quot; I don't find a whole lot of threads in the original 173 article that point to this; it's never mentioned to be shitting or eating, which you would think would be easily observable in its documentation if that's what were going on. So it doesn't really have any means of narrative support outside of itself.</p>

